The paper deals with property testing and data streaming algorithms in the setting of general graphs, which are fundamental topics in computer science. The use of canonical testers and the emulation of constant-query testers in the streaming setting suggest a focus on algorithms and data structures, which are central to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-categories. The paper also deals with graph properties, which are relevant to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category. The use of space constraints in the streaming model suggests a focus on information theory, which is relevant to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. Finally, the use of techniques to handle high-degree vertices suggests a focus on machine learning, which is relevant to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category.
